<title>SINGAPORE: Keppel reopens rescued Philippines bank.</title>
<headline>Keppel reopens rescued Philippines bank.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Singapore conglomerate Keppel Corp Ltd said on Thursday it had reopened all 31 branches of the ailing Monte de Piedad and Savings Bank in the Philippines that it stepped in to rescue last week.</p>
<p>Monte de Piedad had received pledges for substantial deposits on Thursday morning and received an assurance from the Archdiocese of Manila that all church deposits would remain with the bank, Keppel Corp said in a statement.</p>
<p>Keppel Corp has committed 2.5 billion pesos (US$94.8 million) to the bank, 1.5 billion of which is being used for rehabilitation funding.  </p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703011)</p>
